\f1\b Clarity and Directness in Serious Discussions:
\f0\b0  When the conversation turns serious (whether the subject is logistical, emotional, or informational), the author\'92s style trims down the play. He drops most of the emojis and quirky spellings, opting for clearer sentence structure. In a serious planning talk or problem-solving mode, his messages read more plain and procedural. For example, coordinating care for a family member, he writes: 
\f2\i \'93We just stay in one room so we\'92re not using as much energy\'85 Also we never ever leave it on if we aren\'92t in the room\'94
\f0\i0 . These sentences are straightforward, with no \'93lol\'94 or exaggeration \'96 he\'92s conveying factual info to assuage concern (in this case, explaining heater use to (presumably) his mom). Even with his girlfriend, when discussing something like finances or health seriously, he uses a measured tone: 
\f2\i \'93It\'92s fine, I just need you to drive safely\'85 Even if you need to pull over\'94
\f0\i0 . Here he uses polite urgency (\'93please\'85 safely\'94) but not humor; the focus is clarity and emphasis on the important point. In serious mood, he also tends to use punctuation 
\f2\i conventionally
